     People have and always will debate that they have THE ANSWER or the KEY TO A HAPPY LIFE, when in reality, its all bullshit. No one person can say that they have the answer for everyone if a certain lifestyle makes them happy, since we are all unique. People have to find answers for themselves. People tend to be happier when left to their own devices and pursuits, even when others don't agree. Even if a behavior is considered to be deviant by one school of thought, it maybe perfectly acceptable in another. The only thing Humans can agree on is that we will disagree with each other. Knowing that ultimately, someone is going to disagree with any particular thing you might do reguardless of what it is, you might as well just do what you want and say to hell with everyone else since you are the one living your life. If you want to be obnoxious about it, hey, its your life. As long as you respect what other people believe is the best way to go about things in order to live a full happy life, and concentrate on your own happiness, things are much easier.<br>
<br>
My point? If I have one its this: Stop debating life and just live it. Clock is ticking, folks.<br>
