<br>
Leviticus 20, verse 13:  "If a man lies with a man as one lies with a woman, both of them have done what is detestable.  They must be put to death; their blood will be on their own heads."<br>
<br>
However, if you ask any Christian, they'll tell you that Christ's death and resurection absolved the people of following the laws of the old testamnet, including the ten commandments and all of the laws of Leviticus.  New laws were then  set in place by Christ throughout the new testament.<br>
<br>
1 Corinthians 6, verse 9: "Do you not know that the wicked will not inherit the kingdom of God?  Do not be deceived:  Neither the sexually immoral nor idolaters nor adulterers nor male prostitutes nor homosexual offenders ... will inherit the kingdom of God."<br>
<br>
A -true- Christian knows it is not his place to sentance peole, to claim what anothers rights and privelages are.  As a tax-paying citizen, you have, in the United States, the right to do whatever you damn well please.  If I have to, I'll die to defend that right.  If Tim wants to ram his midsection into the netherregions of Tom, go for it.  If Jenny wants to grab a strap-on and have an all-night lube session with Sarah, you go girl.<br>
<br>
However, it is my sworn duty as a confirmed Child of Christ to do whatever is in my power to sway Homosexuals, rapists, murderers, thieves, and any unbeliever to the "light of Christ."  Do I do this 24/7?  Do I door to door evangelize?  Hell no, I've got other things to do with my time, like play EQ.  But if the opportunity presents itself, like right now...<br>
<br>
I've lived with the knowledge of Christ for most of my life.  For a good 19 years of my life, "Christianity" was just something I had to get up early on a sunday morning for and dress up nice.  It wasn't until about two years that I actually sat and thought about it.<br>
<br>
Some people try to "convert" gay people because they find it distasteful.  Some do it because it's "deviant."  Some people just do it because it gives them someone to look down on.  Makes them feel important.<br>
<br>
I do it because I feel the presence of Christ in my every day life.  The comforting knowledge that -no- matter how shitty life ever gets, no matter what horrible stuff happens to me or my closest family and friends, in the end, it'll all be washed away, and eternal bliss and happiness is there for my family and friends to share for the live everlasting.<br>
<br>
I myself am far from perfect.  I've stolen, I've lied, I've harmed others, I've lusted, I've slandered, the list goes on.  But so long as I recognize my wickedness and in my heart repent, I believe that salvation and that the life everlasting is mine through the words and deeds of Christ, I'm forgiven.<br>
<br>
-That- is why -many- Christians out there strive to convince others that homosexuality is a choice.  It's easier to deny your sexual urges if you think of them as a choice rather then a lifestyle.<br>
<br>
I'll probably never be able to quite lying to others, or saying hurtful things.  But I know they're wrong and I shouldn't do them.  If someone is equally addicted to homosexual intercourse, then there's not much one can do.  However, if I can make that person see that it is indeed a sin, and one that they need to repent of, I've done my job.<br>
<br>
People think that knowing about your sins brings about a great depression in people.  I'm telling you that it isn't that way.  In fact, the warmth I feel in knowing Christ overrides any evil I may ever do.<br>
<br>
If you want, you can hold a gun to my head and tell me to stop trying to help "sinners" find redemption.  I'll just smile and quote perhaps my most beloved passage, the first I ever learned.<br>
<br>
John 3, verse 16:  "For God so loved the world that he gave his one and only son, that whoever believes in him shall not perish, but have eternal life." <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35824><img src=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/brain.gif></a><br>
